    p.Article-Paragraph.
      Generates such value of the #[+Term--YDID HTML attribute] #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID href] for the
        #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID a] #[+Term--YDID tag] as once final link has been clicked or tapped,
        the email software will be opened and it will be suggested to submit the new email to the address specified
        via #[+Keyphrase--YDID single] #[+Term--YDID parameter].

    p.Article-Paragraph.
      All that this #[+Term--YDID function] doing is appending the #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID mailto:] to the
        specified #[+Term--YDID string value] which expected to be the valid email address.
      If your text editor of the #[+Term--YDID Integrated Development Environment] (#[+Term--YDID IDE]) have
        #[+Keyword--YDID no] the functionality of the autocompleting according the templates, this #[+Term--YDID function]
        hardly will be useful for you: #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID mailto:] or
        the #[+Term--YDID function] name #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID buildEmailLinkHrefAttributeValue], you will
        need either to memorize it or check the reference guide every time.

    p.Article-Paragraph
      | If the autocompletion by the templates functionality is presents, it is enough to begin to input
      |   #[+SecondaryEntity__Code--YDID buildE...], then the popup hint will appear and the further actions depends
      |   on how the autocomplete has been implemented in the text editor or #[+Term--YDID IDE].
      | In the case of the
      |
      +Link--YDF({ unendorsedExternalURI: sharedExternalLinks.jetBrains.liveTemplates }).Article-Link Live Templates
      |   from the
      |
      +Link--YDF({ unendorsedExternalURI: sharedExternalLinks.jetBrains.YDF_Plugin }).Article-Link official YDF plugin
      |   for the
      |
      +Link--YDF({ unendorsedExternalURI: sharedExternalLinks.jetBrains.intelliJ_IDEA_FamilyIDEs }).Article-Link.
        IntelliJ IDEA family IDEs
      |   the automatic inserting of the value #[+Keyword--YDID preliminary] copied to the clipboard to the position
      |   of the #[+Keyword--YDID single] #[+Term--YDID parameter] is being executed.
      | Thus, the inputting of the #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID href] #[+Term--YDID attribute] using the
